The life of our Karimikui coffeeüòª
When it comes to coffee production, our experience with Kenyan coffee was so rooted in community. Lots of these coffees are grown in families‚Äô backyards or microlots, where the operations are so small there is no way they could have their own processing mills or equipment. But the structure here is set up in a way where all these families can come together and use the same equipment, build relationships with each other, and produce an amazing product. Everybody wins!üò∫
.
Farmers walk or drive the cherries to their local factory (wet mill), where the cherries are washed and dried and taken to the Run‚Äôgeto Co-op for dry mill processing. Then Ibero Kenya and @interamericancoffee bring us this amazing product to serve, paying a solid price to the families who made it happen at all. We fall in love, roast it up and the rest is historyü§ôüèº

New mugs on the web handmade by our very own @kellymbeachüî•Our team members are talented, dynamic humans with a lot of passions outside of work. Kelly hand-throws and paints ceramics, slings a mean espresso, met her fianc√© in our caf√©, and also teaches ballet here in town! Every person working in our rad industry has a story and a life when they‚Äôre on the other side of the counter‚Äîone that‚Äôs pretty amazing if you just get an opportunity to see it. The more we can showcase that to the world, the better.üíô link in photo to check out these mugs, there‚Äôs only 25 so be warned!üî•

‚ö°Ô∏èNEW COFFEE‚ö°Ô∏è
We‚Äôve got three new coffees in the caf√©s and online today, wahoo! If you want some quick flavor notes, swipe on over. But like most coffees we get, they‚Äôve got some fun stories behind them too.üò∫ So read on for a good one:
.
We sent Levi and Foy to Colombia a few months ago to judge in Best Cup and buy their favorite green coffee for the caf√©. They loved this washed Castillo by Jairo Bomba that placed 12th out of 1300(!), but it was getting lowkey slept on in the auction, in favor of the ‚Äúbig 10‚Äù coming after. To everyone else‚Äôs confusion, our two baristas started a bidding war with each other to deliberately drive up the price of the coffeeüòπ
.
WHY? They thought it deserved more. They wanted to pay Jairo the higher price he deserved for his family‚Äôs hard work, even if it means we pay more for it on our end. Jairo‚Äôs happy, we‚Äôre happy, and numbers 11 through 1 are happy too because we were able set a standard for pricing for all the coffees that came after this. Thanks for representing our mission well, guysüò∏ Leaving people happier than they found them, 2016 ‚Äòtil ‚úäüèº

The bigger we get as a company, the harder it seems to get everyone physically in one place, which we love to do to calibrate and stay on the same page. But sometimes the stars align, the vibe is right, and you just have those nights where you remember that the culture really is so alive. Our last orientation night was like that.üíô Only five of these faces are actually new! The rest just voluntarily took their Tuesday night to welcome new friends, support old ones, & get that vision alignment that keeps us all going. It‚Äôs all 20/20 going forward and things are looking pretty bright y‚Äôallü§©
.
Thank you to everyone who has been welcoming our new staff into your ‚Äúhome caf√©‚Äù & our community. We appreciate you, SCüëäüèº

Growing a wholesale business is a hot topic in coffee‚Äîand although of course it‚Äôs exciting to see this side of the business grow, the intention behind it here has always been to find like-minded companies that we mesh with, instead of pushing for specific numerical goals. Strong values and a shared outlook have made all the difference for us in forming long-term partnerships that go further than payments or accounts. And because of that, we‚Äôve been able to make friends with some pretty amazing businesses and humans!
.
Who wants to party next? #ROADTRIP üòª Thanks again, we üíô u @goodsidecoffee!

‚ÄúThe beautiful thing about coffee is that it allows our team to get to connect with and build relationships with policy makers at the state, city and county levels to creatives, artists, students, and world changers. Sacramento's coffee culture also lends itself to being unique in the sense that its strong, healthy and thriving. I think we're very lucky to have that here.‚Äù
.
Sacramento is a special city to call home and our partners @goodsidecoffee have such an authentic love for it‚Äîthis is the kind of vision we are so here for.üíô We‚Äôre heading up to Sac this FRIDAY to do a bar takeover from 11-1‚Äîswing by and kick it with Marc & Alex from wholesale and Sam from IG! We‚Äôll be slinging spro, making friends and sharing the love with our Sacramento family. See you thenüòª

üò∫xüíÄ: the collab.üî•üî• We just spent the first half of our week serving coffee at a conference in SF, with help from our brother Ev of @calaveracoffee, and wow was it rad! Espresso was slung, our voices are gone, and the fun/exhaustion dials were both turned up to 11, leggoüò∏

üëãüèº 2020! A lot can change in a year, huh? This photo is a bit of a throwback from beautiful summer days with our downtown crew. Hard to believe so much time has passed but now our mvp @coffeefreckled is about to have a freakin BABY and our bold adventurer @emallisart is on staff at a college in indigenous Alaskaü§Ø We miss ‚Äòem!
.
Having team members grow into new phases of life is so relevant to our mission‚Äîleaving people better than we found them doesn‚Äôt apply only to our guests. That ‚Äúleaving‚Äù could be after a year moving into a new industry, it could be after a few years and moving up within our leadership structure, or it could be choosing to stay for a long-ass time and haul along with us as we change the world with positive vibes! But no matter what it looks like, we need to be caring for every one in a way that has them leaving TRULY better off. Equipped with new job skills for life, newfound confidence in themselves and their value, authentic friendships to carry along forever...let‚Äôs do all of that and more.
.
Tag your previous team members you love and appreciate below. Or tag your previous employer who made a difference for you! Let‚Äôs spread the love today.‚ô•Ô∏èü§üüèºüëáüèº

Meet Damian Chavez! He‚Äôs an extremely special person to our company and if you‚Äôve been around at all, you‚Äôve probably seen his name on our coffee bags all year round. He took over his coffee farm in Honduras at just about the same time that we opened up shop (so, we‚Äôre both toddlers together) and processes all his coffees with his family at their home. And time and time again, he straight-up blows us all out of the water, not only with the coffee itself but with his integrity and values.
.
Damian‚Äôs been nominated as Notable Producer by @sprudge and I‚Äôll speak for us all here when I say it‚Äôs more than well-deserved.
.
Since meeting Damian in 2018 we‚Äôve become the exclusive purchaser of all his farm lots throughout the year. These partnerships are beneficial for both sides from a business standpoint but it‚Äôs really about so much more than that. It doesn‚Äôt have to be about commodity and the c market, it‚Äôs about relationships; the more that we go forward together, the more we all grow, and the better we are all left from it. Vote for him on @sprudge, link‚Äôs in our bio! Cheersüíô

Podcasting on the floor: it‚Äôs a vibe.‚ú® It‚Äôs been 4 and a half years of podding every single week‚Äîjust looked it up and we‚Äôre at # 234! Pretty nutsüòπ

.

Caf√© lifeüíô the routine on both sides of the counter can be a little like Groundhog Day but I think we can all forget what a special impact baristas have in the universe. Behind the drinks is all the real shit. Being someone‚Äôs very first conversation and setting the tone for the day. Reading human emotions and meeting people where they‚Äôre at‚Äîhappy, sad, ticked off, whatever. Creating a space where everyone feels seen and included. And yes‚Äîfocusing on all those tedious details of the job too, details someone might not even realize were intentional but that make them walk out the door feeling pretty dang good. It‚Äôs a big job when it‚Äôs done right! Cheers to the day-makers todayüëäüèºüò∫

Although we‚Äôre thankful for you all every day, it‚Äôs worth mentioning again today.üò∫ From our locs in Santa Cruz, to all of you in the US, to our friends around the world!üåè‚Äîyour support and positivity makes more of a difference than you know & let us become what we are today. If you ever get a chance to visit Santa Cruz, come on in and join the fam. We‚Äôve always got a place at the table for you and plenty of loveüíô happy Thanksgiving y‚Äôall!

Having a bomb & healthy company culture is kind of like all of our funny secret handshakes. We intentionally decide what we want it to look like, and then put it into practice by actually *doing* it everytime we see each other. After long enough, things are so natural it seems like it was always there. But it takes plenty of intentionality to get to that pointüò∫
.
Don‚Äôt forget that the work you‚Äôre putting in is worth it, and is all contributing to the culture and values you love.üíô Tag your secret handshake partner below and enjoy your holiday weekend ahead, friends!üò∫ü§úüèºü§õüèº

Sending our team members to Origin is about more than coffee tasting. When we go:

‚Ä¢ We experience the way coffee affects entire communities as a livelihood and culture
‚Ä¢ Some of us who may not have been entrusted with big decisions in our past get to step up & trust in what we‚Äôve learned, to taste, judge, and purchase coffees for the year ahead
‚Ä¢ We represent our company culture & absorb as much as we can from the people around us
‚Ä¢ We take our own weird, unique personalities and put them out there in the world to make people happier and spread the love!
